      {
        "id": "6aa29bf960cfd2e41bc8df3060bce63fee3a9760",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2815,
          "name": "Michal Kabaj",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
          "username": "kabayashi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-23 14:23:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Takamune,\nI did not find any relation between DG and RequestContext class. \nThe RequestContext class is used on a local, method-scoped level and does not expose its api, outside the module. Also there seem to be multiple copies of this class inside other modules and there we can see that the api methods of thoses copies are used explicitly inside certain inside other classes (while still maintaining the method scope). If I am missing something then let me know. I do not seen any way the classes could be used without outside of the module without any context-wise declaration or framework based injection. Rather the life of the object seems to be completely local. If this indeed is somehow used without clear indication from inside the code and module configuration, then this ambiguity may hint a serious design flaw and technical debt.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
